Wale Fapohunda, Convener of The Green Alliance Movement, has said that the Governor of the Central bank of Nigeria (CBN), Godwin Emefiele, is the right man to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari in 2o23. Fapohunda insisted that Emefiele has the capacity for modern day leadership and to be the president of Nigeria.
Fapohunda is leading The Green Alliance Movement in demanding that the CBN governor, Godwin Emefiele, joins the presidential race in 2023.
The Green Alliance Movement is perceived to be doing the ground networking in the south, while the Unified Northern Nigeria Youth Forum (UNNYF) is traversing the north mobilizing support for Emefiele.
